+      7: ## Architecture
+      8: 
+      9: ```
+     10: content bytes
+     11:       │
+     12:       ▼
+     13: ┌─────────────┐
+     14: │  FileAdder  │  rust-unixfs crate (git submodule: vendor/rust-ipfs)
+     15: │  (UnixFS    │  Encodes content as dag-pb protobuf blocks.
+     16: │   dag-pb)   │  Chunks large files into a balanced Merkle DAG.
+     17: └──────┬──────┘
+     18:        │ yields (CID, block_bytes) pairs
+     19:        ▼
+     20: ┌─────────────┐
+     21: │ write_block │  Writes each block to go-ipfs flatfs:
+     22: │  (flatfs)   │    ~/.ipfs/blocks/{shard}/{key}.data
+     23: └──────┬──────┘
+     24:        │ returns root CID
+     25:        ▼
+     26: ┌─────────────┐
+     27: │ paste header│  Stored as IPFS: QmcFFn... in paste file
+     28: │  + JSON API │  Returned as ipfs_cid in POST /paste response
+     29: └─────────────┘
+     30: ```
+     31: 
+     32: ## Flatfs Layout
+     33: 
+     34: go-ipfs stores blocks in a sharded directory tree under `~/.ipfs/blocks/`.
+     35: The sharding scheme is **next-to-last/2**:
+     36: 
+     37: ```
+     38: key   = BASE32_NOPAD_UPPER(multihash)
+     39: shard = key[len-3 .. len-1]   (2nd-to-last two characters)
+     40: path  = ~/.ipfs/blocks/{shard}/{key}.data
+     41: ```
+     42: 
+     43: Example for `QmcFFnmxaUcMiF7ePCtqndf7rfZzsG6jrW46gDM7ToD2q9`:
+     44: 
+     45: ```
+     46: multihash = 1220... (0x12=sha256, 0x20=32 bytes, then digest)
+     47: key       = CIQO...XY
+     48: shard     = last-2-before-last char of key
+     49: path      = ~/.ipfs/blocks/XY/CIQO...XY.data
+     50: ```
+     51: 
+     52: ## CID Versions
+     53: 
+     54: - **CIDv0** (`Qm...`): Returned by `FileAdder` (base58btc, dag-pb + sha256).
