Text-to-Speech (TTS) Implementation
The SpeechSynthesis interface allows web pages to generate text-to-speech output using available system voices. 
MDN Web Docs
MDN Web Docs
Create a SpeechSynthesisUtterance: This object represents the text you want to be spoken and can be configured with properties like voice, pitch, and rate.
javascript
let speech = new SpeechSynthesisUtterance();
speech.text = "Hello, world!";
Use window.speechSynthesis.speak(): Pass the utterance object to the speak() method to start the speech.
javascript
window.speechSynthesis.speak(speech);
 
