Recording the Audio
Recording the audio generated by the TTS requires a different approach, as the Web Speech API doesn't inherently provide a direct audio file output for the synthesized speech itself. To record the output, you typically use the MediaStream Recording API. This often involves capturing the entire browser's audio output (which is complex and not standard browser JS) or, more practically, using a dedicated recording library if the browser doesn't offer a direct way to download the audio. 
