Using a library or service that generates an audio file (e.g., MP3/WAV) from the text on the server side.
Or, in some niche cases, capturing the audio stream from the browser's audio context using specific APIs, which can be complex to implement across all browsers. 
For most standard browser JS projects, the TTS function is for live playback, not for generating recordable audio files within the browser without additional complex APIs or external services. 
