+    23: 
+    24: ## What It Tests
+    25: 
+    26: | # | Test | What it checks |
+    27: |---|------|----------------|
+    28: | 1 | Page loads | WASM initializes, title contains "eRDFa" |
+    29: | 2 | Input text | Setting textarea value works |
+    30: | 3 | Morse encode | `doMorseEnc()` produces correct morse output |
+    31: | 4 | Numbers station | `doNumEnc()` decimal encoding |
+    32: | 5 | Stego encode (default) | DCT stego encode on placekitten 256×256 carrier |
+    33: | 6 | Stego decode (default) | Roundtrip: decoded text matches original |
+    34: | 7 | Stego upload + roundtrip | Load 128×128 PNG via data URL, encode "stego ok!" (9/14 byte capacity), decode matches |
+    35: | 8 | QR encode | `doQrEnc()` generates QR + saves to IPFS |
+    36: | 9 | Base64 roundtrip | Encode → decode recovers original text |
+    37: | 10 | IPFS localStorage | `doStore()` stores paste by CID |
+    38: | 11 | No JS errors | No uncaught exceptions |
+    39: 
+    40: Screenshot saved to `/tmp/erdfa-test-screenshot.png`.
+    41: 
+    42: ## How It Works
+    43: 
+    44: - **Nix flake** provides: Rust toolchain, Chromium, Xvfb, chromedriver, openssl
+    45: - **Xvfb** provides a virtual X display (Chromium needs one even in headless mode)
+    46: - **`file://`** loads the pad directly from disk — no HTTP server needed
+    47: - **`--allow-file-access-from-files`** lets the WASM module load via `file://` protocol
+    48: - **`headless_chrome`** Rust crate drives Chromium via DevTools Protocol
+    49: - **`CHROME_BIN`** env var points the crate at the nix-provided Chromium binary
+    50: 
+    51: ## Key Flags
+    52: 
+    53: ```
+    54: --allow-file-access-from-files  # WASM fetch works over file://
+    55: --no-sandbox                    # Required in nix/container environments
+    56: --disable-gpu                   # No GPU in headless
+    57: --disable-dev-shm-usage         # Avoid /dev/shm size issues
+    58: --ignore-certificate-errors     # For HTTPS testing if needed
+    59: ```
+    60: 
+    61: ## Stego Capacity Reference
+    62: 
+    63: | Image Size | Capacity (bytes) | Notes |
+    64: |------------|-----------------|-------|
+    65: | 128×128 | 14 | Very short messages only |
+    66: | 256×256 | ~73 | Default placekitten carrier |
+    67: | 512×512 | ~292 | Good for paragraphs |
+    68: | 1024×1024 | ~1170 | ~1KB payload |
+    69: 
+    70: Formula: `floor(floor(w/8) * floor(h/8) * 4 / 7 / 8) - 4`
+    71: (4 DCT coefficients per 8×8 block, 7× ECC redundancy, 4-byte length header)
+    72: 
+    73: ## Troubleshooting
+    74: 
+    75: - **`net::ERR_ABORTED`** — Chromium can't reach the URL. Use `file://` instead of HTTP/HTTPS.
+    76: - **`Authorization required`** — No X display. Start Xvfb first.
+    77: - **WASM functions return null** — Missing `--allow-file-access-from-files` flag.
+    78: - **`⚠️ Data too large!`** — Message exceeds carrier capacity. Use a larger image.
+    79: - **WASM MIME type** — nginx needs `types { application/wasm wasm; }` in the `/erdfa/` location block.
