+      1: # eRDFa Library — Embeddable Sneakernet Encoder/Decoder
+      2: 
+      3: Embeddable WASM-powered widget that adds encoding, RDFa discovery, and annotation to any web page. One script tag gives you a floating popup with morse, base64, QR, steganography, and RDFa tools.
+      4: 
+      5: ## Quick Start
+      6: 
+      7: Add to any HTML page:
+      8: 
+      9: ```html
+     10: <script type="module" src="https://solana.solfunmeme.com/erdfa/erdfa-lib.js"></script>
+     11: ```
+     12: 
+     13: A 🔐 button appears in the bottom-right corner. Click to open the panel.
+     14: 
+     15: ## Features
+     16: 
+     17: | Feature | Description |
+     18: |---------|-------------|
+     19: | 📡 Morse | Encode/decode text as morse code |
+     20: | 📦 Base64 | Base64 encode/decode |
+     21: | 📱 QR | QR code generation |
+     22: | 🔍 RDFa Scan | Discover all RDFa annotations on the current page |
+     23: | ✏️ Annotate | Select text → add RDFa `property` attribute |
+     24: | 📋 Copy | Copy encoded output to clipboard |
+     25: 
+     26: ## JavaScript API
+     27: 
+     28: The library exposes `window.erdfa` with these methods:
+     29: 
+     30: ```javascript
+     31: // Panel control
+     32: erdfa.open()      // Open the popup
+     33: erdfa.close()     // Close the popup
+     34: erdfa.toggle()    // Toggle open/close
+     35: 
+     36: // Encoding
+     37: erdfa.morse()     // Encode input as morse
+     38: erdfa.b64()       // Encode input as base64
+     39: erdfa.qr()        // Encode input as QR payload
+     40: 
+     41: // RDFa
+     42: erdfa.scan()      // Discover RDFa on the page (property, typeof, about, resource)
+     43: erdfa.annotate()  // Wrap selected text in <span property="...">
+     44: 
+     45: // Utilities
+     46: erdfa.grab()      // Pull browser selection into the input field
+     47: erdfa.copy()      // Copy output to clipboard
+     48: erdfa.val()       // Get current input value
+     49: erdfa.set(id, v)  // Set element innerHTML
+     50: ```
+     51: 
+     52: ## RDFa Discovery
+     53: 
+     54: `erdfa.scan()` finds all elements with RDFa attributes:
+     55: - `property` — schema.org or custom properties
+     56: - `typeof` — RDFa type declarations
+     57: - `about` — subject URIs
+     58: - `resource` — object URIs
+     59: 
+     60: Results display in the panel with property names and content previews.
+     61: 
+     62: ## RDFa Annotation
+     63: 
+     64: 1. Select text on the page
+     65: 2. Enter a property name (e.g. `schema:name`, `dc:title`)
+     66: 3. Click "Add RDFa"
+     67: 
+     68: The selected text gets wrapped in `<span property="schema:name">selected text</span>`.
+     69: 
+     70: ## Architecture
+     71: 
+     72: ```
+     73: erdfa-lib.js          ES module, loads WASM from ./pkg/
+     74:   └── pkg/
+     75:       ├── erdfa_wasm.js       JS bindings (wasm-bindgen)
+     76:       └── erdfa_wasm_bg.wasm  Rust compiled to WASM
+     77: ```
+     78: 
+     79: The library uses `import.meta.url` to resolve the WASM path relative to itself, so it works from any hosting location.
